What's that?
~~~~~~~~~~~~

This tarball contains source snapshots of Nemerle Preliminary Compiler
(npc/) and Nemerle Documentation (doc/).

Nemerle is functional-object-oriented-imperative hybrid programming
language that targets .NET platform.

To find out more, and to get latest version, please visit:

   http://nemerle.org


Build instructions
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

To compile npc you will need OCaml 3.06 (http://www.ocaml.org)
and GNU Make.

Just do:

  $ cd npc
  $ make

To rebuild documentation you will need xsltproc (http://xmlsoft.org) and 
xspp (http://www.kernel.pl/~malekith/xspp). You will also need LaTeX and
probably few styles. You can save yourself effort by downloading:

   http://nemerle.org/download/nemerle-web.tar.gz

that contains all file pre-rendered.


Contact
~~~~~~~

Please check http://nemerle.org for contact instructions.
